- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely category as instance-based methods are used for proof search in first-order logic, which is a major area of research in logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as instance-based methods can be used for program analysis and verification, which are major areas of research in PL. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as instance-based methods can be used for similarity search and classification, which are major areas of research in DS. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as instance-based methods can be used for software testing and verification, which are major areas of research in SE.
